sentences: Ma tean, et see on halb, aga ma ei saa midagi teha, noh.

Ta vaatas mind ja 端tles lihtsalt: "Noh?"
context: The Estonian word 'noh' is an interjection used similarly to 'well', 'you know', or 'so' in English. It often serves as a filler word, indicating hesitation, seeking agreement, or softening a statement. It can also express resignation or acceptance of a situation.
